The paper proposes a framework for multi-agent training using deep deterministic policy gradients and memory-driven communication. This work involves deep learning, reinforcement learning, and multi-agent systems, which are all covered by the arXiv categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.MA (Multiagent Systems), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.SY (Systems and Control). However, since the focus is on deep reinforcement learning and multi-agent coordination, cs.LG and cs.MA are the most likely categories, followed by cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.SY.
